slime;1;Seeming to be a ball of translucent gloop with two randomly pointed eyes. It is a surprise it is around at all because it just rolls around with no aim or goal.;Encountered in the first layer, the slime is a glutonous mass about waist height with two large eyeballs. As the slime rolls around, it picks up small insects and digests it within. It also leaves behind a trail of ooze that pulls up small minerals because of it's acidic nature.
